OL,3,CWhy am I struggling to sleep and what
OL,4,Ccan I do?
OL,6,FThey also revealed that around
OL,7,Ffourteen million people are currently
OL,8,Fliving with an undiagnosed sleep
OL,9,Fdisorder due to the normalisation of
OL,10,Fdisrupted sleep.
OL,12,FSo, why are so many people struggling
OL,13,Fwith sleep disorders?
OL,15,FDr Raman Sakhuja, a sleep
OL,16,Fpsychiatrist, told ITV Wales he has
OL,17,Fseen more people in recent years seek
OL,18,Fhelp for sleep disorders.
OL,20,FHe says that our modern lifestyle
OL,21,Fcould have an impact on how we sleep.
